 example German and Jewish <b>Schäfer</b> (see   Schaefer  )."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]},{"name":"Ann","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Anne .  In the U.S. <i>Ann</i> is the more frequent spelling."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Ann Sheppherd was born about 1523, in Lavenham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Sir John Shepherd. She married John Copsey about 1540, in Bury St Edmunds St Mary, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died about 1580, in Glemsford, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 59."},"et":{"about 1523–about 1580":"umbes 1523–umbes 1580","1523–1580":"1523–1580","1520–1571":"1520–1571","1540–1602":"1540–1602","1543–1575":"1543–1575","1500–Male":"1500–Surnud","about 1580":"umbes 1580","18 May 1571":"18. mai 1571","1 July 1543":"1. juuli 1543","1571":"1571","1580":"1580","1602":"1602","1523":"1523","1500":"1500","1543":"1543","1575":"1575","1520":"1520","about 1523":"umbes 1523","1540":"1540","about 1540":"umbes 1540","after 1575":"pärast 1